SwiftUI's declarative nature makes it easier to manage dependencies using the Swift Package Manager (SPM). SPM integrates seamlessly with Xcode, eliminating the need for third-party tools like CocoaPods and Carthage. However, CocoaPods offers more flexibility in handling multiple frameworks and libraries. Carthage is ideal for managing dependencies in Swift-only projects. When using SPM, specify dependencies in your app's Package.swift file. For example:

import PackageDescription

let package = Package(
    name: "MyApp",
    dependencies: [
        .package(url: "https://github.com/apple/swift-collections.git", from: "1.0.0"),
        .package(url: "https://github.com/JohnSundell/Files.git", from: "1.0.0")
    ]
)

